    <DocumentationNarrative Id="source:cli:meta-pipeline:app:narrative:guide:working-with-metapipeline" DocumentationSubjectId="source:cli:meta-pipeline:app" PreviousNarrativeId="source:cli:meta-pipeline:app:narrative:summary:summary">
      <Body>MetaPipeline models executable work as named pipelines and tasks. A task can be backed by a validated transform or by an explicit executable, with declared dependencies, connection context, timeouts, fingerprints, and the evidence needed to understand each run.

The workspace is the plan. It describes what should be executed and the contracts it relies on. The optional operational database records diagnostics, metrics, audits, and failures, giving an execution a useful history without becoming the source of model truth.

This makes pipeline behavior inspectable before it is scheduled. A team can author steps, review their dependencies and execution context, run a pipeline or individual task, and retain operational evidence that points back to the exact modeled plan.</Body>
      <BodyFormat>Markdown</BodyFormat>
      <Origin>Authored</Origin>
      <ReviewStatus>Current</ReviewStatus>
